            "text": "Fig.\u00a01: Phylogenetic analyses. Phylogenetic trees were generated using six structural (VP1-4, VP6, and VP7) and five non-structural proteins (NSP1-5) of the rotavirus I strain Felis catus, the two species I strains (KE135 and KE528), and representatives of other species in the Rotavirus genus. The scale indicates amino acid substitutions per position. Bootstrap values (based on 100 replicates) for each node are given if >70. The amino acid identity (%) between rotavirus I strain Felis catus and KE135 or KE528 are included in the trees",
